'''Sophia Rabliauskas''' is an environmental activist and member of the [[Poplar River First Nation]] in [[Manitoba]], [[Canada]]. She was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 2007 for her efforts to secure protection of two million acres (8,000&nbsp;km²) of undisturbed forests in the boreal region of Manitoba.<ref name=goldman>{{cite web |url= https://www.goldmanprize.org/recipient/sophia-rabliauskas/ |title= Sophia Rabliauskas. 2007 Goldman Prize Recipient |website= goldmanprize.org |access-date= 26 May 2018 }}</ref> 

She was decorated Member of the [[Order of Manitoba]] in 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/people/orderofmanitoba.shtml#r |title= Members of the Order of Manitoba |website= mhs.mb.ca |access-date= 26 May 2018 }}</ref>

